Multiple Chart Areas Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>Essential Chart uses a custom grid to host multiple areas within a chart. This usually results in a single-column, multi-row layout of the different chart areas. However, you can replace the built-in grid host with any panel-derived class for hosting different chart areas. This sample illustrates the use of the following panel-derived types that are used to host multiple chart areas.</Paragraph><List MarkerStyle="Disc"><ListItem><Paragraph>Grid</Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph>Dock Panel</Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph>Wrap Panel</Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph>Canvas</Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph>Stack Panel</Paragraph><Paragraph>Carousel Panel</Paragraph></ListItem></List><Paragraph><Run xml:space="preserve">The following image illustrates the use of a </Run><Run FontWeight="Bold" xml:space="preserve">Carousel Panel </Run>to host three different chart areas.</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/Custom Panel Demo.png" Width="750" Height="520"/></Paragraph>

